College: Jagadguru Dattatray College of Technology, Indore
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
Eigibility-1st Year XII with : Phy + Maths + (Chem. / Comp. Sc./Bio) with Min. 50% (45 % for SC/ST/OBC) with qualified rank in PET
2nd Year Direct Admission : 1. Min. 50% (45% for SC/ST/OBC) Diploma in Engg.
2. With at least 60% in B. Sc (with Maths)
For - CG Student The branch wise intakes are reserved for State Quota, All India Quota & Management Quota. The percentages of various quotas are decided by the State Government. However, the current proportions are State Quota: 75%, All India Quota: 10% and Management Quota: 15%. For admission under State Quota, a candidate is expected to qualify in PET conducted by Professional Examination Board, Chhattisgarh (CGVYAPAM). Thereafter, candidates having domicile of Chhattisgarh State are called for counseling by Directorate of Technical Education, Govt. of Chhattisgarh and according to availability at the time of counseling seats are allotted. For admission under All India Quota, a candidate is expected to qualify in AIEEE conducted by CBSE, New Delhi. Thereafter, candidates are called for counseling by Directorate of Technical Education, Govt. of Chhattisgarh and according to availability at the time of counseling seats are allotted. For admission under Management Quota, a candidate is expected to qualify either in PET conducted by Professional Examination Board, Chhattisgarh (CGVYAPAM) or AIEEE conducted by CBSE, New Delhi. Advertisement is placed in Newspapers and also in the website for admission (after the declaration of the results of the entrance examinations) under Management Quota and the list is finalized strictly based on merit of the entrance examinations.
Course_Detail: BE Civil Engineeringis a full-time four years duration course Affiliated to Rajiv Gandhi Proudyogiki Vishwavidyalaya, Bhopal and Approved by AICTE.

Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
Passed 10+2 examination of CHSE, Odisha or equivalent with Physics and Mathematics as compulsory subjects along with one of the subjects from Chemistry / Biotechnology / Biology / Electronics / Computer Science / Information Technology / Geology / Statistics. The candidate should have passed individual subject and must have obtained at least 45% marks (40% in case of candidate belonging to SC/ST category) in the above subjects taken together.
OR,
Passed in diploma examination in Engineering / Technology from State Council of Technical Education and Training (SCTE&VT;), Odisha or equivalent with at least 45% marks (40% in case of candidate belonging to SC/ST category) in the qualifying examination in appropriate branch of Engineering / Technology for direct admission to the third semester degree courses in Engineering / Technology.

College: Focus Institute of Science and Technology, Poomala
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
Candidates who have passed Higher Secondary Examination, Kerala or recognized as equivalent there to, with 50% marks in Mathematics separately and 50% marks in Mathematics, Physics and chemistry put together are eligible for admission. However, candidates who have obtained 45% marks in Mathematics separately with 60% aggregate marks in Physics and Chemistry put together are also eligible for admission.
OR,
Candidates belonging to socially and Educationally Backward Classes with a total annual family income not exceeding Rs.6 Lakhs,need 45 % marks in the case of Mathematics separately and 45% marks for Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics put together. The Scheduled Caste and Scheduled Tribe candidates need only a pass mark in the qualifying examination.
OR,
Socially and Educationally backward Classes (SEBC) within the income limit prescribed above/Persons with Disabilities (PD) category candidates who have obtained 40% marks in Mathematics separately with 55% aggregate marks in Physics and Chemistry put together are also eligible for admission.

Candidates seeking admission to the first year of the four year B.E. degree course in Engineering shall be required to have anyone of the following eligibilities A pass in Higher Secondary Course (Academic) with Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry.A Pass in Higher Secondary Course (Vocational) in Engineering/Technology and one of the related subjects with Mathematics/Physics/Chemistry as related subject. Not withstanding the qualifying examination the candidate might have passed, the candidate should also have written the entrance examination designed to test the proficiency of the candidate in Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry with standards prescribed for plus two academic stream of the Tamil Nadu Board of Higher Secondary Education.
ADMISSION TO DIRECT SECOND YEAR B.E / B.TECH ( Lateral Entry)
A pass in Diploma in Engineering of the State Board of Technical Education and training, Tamilnadu or its equalent. However, the candidate should have scored the requisites minimum proscribed aggregate marks of 60%

Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
Passed 10+2 Examination with Physics & Mathematics as compulsory subjects alongwith one of Chemistry / Biology and has obtained atleast 45% marks (42.75% in case of candidates belonging to reserved category) in the above subjects taken together.
Lateral Entry to second year of B.Tech Program for the Candidates with following Eligibility : –
A. Passed Diploma Examination from an AICTE approved Institution ; with atleast 50% marks ( 45% in case of candidates belonging to reserved category) in appropriate brances of Engineering / Technology.
B. Passed B.Sc. Degree from a recognized university as defined by UGC, with at least 50% marks ( 45% in case of candidates belonging to reserved category) and Passed XII standard with mathematics as a subject.
C. Provided that the students belonging to B.Sc. Stream, shall clear the subjects of Engineering Mechanics of the first year engineering program along with the second year subjects.
D. Provided further that the students belonging to B.Sc Stream shall be considered only after filling the supplementary seats in this category with students belonging to the diploma stream.
E. Provided further that the students, who have passed Diploma in Engineering & Technology from an AICTE approved institution or B.Sc. Degree from a recognised university as defined by UGC shall also be eligible for admission to the first year Engineering Degree Courses subject to the condition that vacancies at lateral entry are exhausted. However the admissions shall be based strictly on the eligibility criteria as mentioned in A,B, D and E above.
Course_Detail: Bachelor of Technology in Civil Engineering is a full-time four-year course affiliated to Kurukshetra University, Kurukshetra and approved by AICTE

Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
The candidates who passed X standard or equivalent examinations with Mathematics and Science subjects are eligible for admission into polytechnic colleges.
There is no age restriction to join the Diploma Courses with effect from the academic year 2004-2005.
For Lateral entry into the second year (III Semester) of the three year diploma courses, the candidates shall be required to have passed the Higher Secondary Examination (Vocational) of 10 and +2 pattern or ITI (must have passed SSLC & two year ITI)
Students passing 12th Science with Vocational/ Technical subjects or Xth +(2 years ITI) with appropriate specialization in that order shall be eligible for admission to second year.
Vocational Stream candidates should have studied either Maths or Physics or Chemistry as one of the subjects of study along with the related vocational subjects (Theory & Practical ) at 10 and +2 level. There is no age limit for the admission.

Eligiblity:
The candidates who have passed the Standard X examination are eligible for admission for Polytechnic Colleges. Before the admission process is started, the required qualifications such as Age, Marks required, and Number of Seats in the various categories etc. are checked so that students can decide their choice of Course etc. well in advance.
Lateral Entry Admissions
HSC (Academic & Vocational)and ITI(2 years NCVT courses) students can directly join in the second year of the three year Diploma programme under the Lateral Entry System in Polytechnics. Their intake is restricted to 20% (10% Academic + 10% Vocational) of the sanctioned intake of the 1 year Diploma courses.

candidate passing HSC examination (Std.
